Hi Todd.

Keep in mind that those extra activations in HyperNEAT are in the CPPN and
not in the final neural net (called the &#39;substrate&#39;). For example, your
stock data would never be passed through a Gaussian (unless you changed
HyperNEAT to allow that as a possible activation function in the substrate).




